## BETTING SYSTEMS & STRATEGIES

### MARTINGALE SYSTEM

#### Original Martingale (Double after loss)
```
Bet sequence: 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, ...
After n losses: Bet = 2^n
Win after n losses: Profit = 1
```

```asciimath
#### Probability of Ruin (Martingale)
```
P(ruin) = 1 - (1 - p^N)  where p = probability of loss, N = number of losses before ruin
For fair coin flip (p=0.5): P(ruin) = 1 - (1/2)^N
With finite bankroll B: P(ruin) = (q/p)^B / (1 - (q/p)^(B+1)) where q = 1-p
```

#### Expected Number of Trials
```
E[trials to win] = 1/(1-p)
```

#### Required Bankroll
```
Bankroll needed for N-step Martingale = 2^N - 1 units
```

### ANTI-MARTINGALE (PAROLI SYSTEM)

#### Double after win
```
Bet sequence after win: 1, 2, 4, 8, ...
Stop after predetermined number of wins or loss
```

#### Expected Value
```
EV = p^N × (2^N - 1) - (1 - p^N) × 1
```

### D'ALEMBERT SYSTEM

#### Increase by 1 after loss, decrease by 1 after win
```
Bet_n = Bet_1 + (Losses - Wins)
```

#### Expected Value
```
EV = 0 for fair game (no house edge)
```

### FIBONACCI SYSTEM

#### Bet sequence follows Fibonacci numbers
```
Bet sequence: 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, ...
After loss: move two steps right
After win: move one step left
```

### LABOUCHERE SYSTEM (CANCELLATION)

#### Write sequence, bet sum of ends
```
Sequence: 1, 2, 3, 4
Bet = 1 + 4 = 5
Win: Cross off ends (1 and 4)
Loss: Add bet amount to end (1, 2, 3, 4, 5)
```

