## PIECE MOVEMENT MATRICES

### BOARD REPRESENTATION
```
Board = 8×8 matrix B[i][j] where i,j ∈ {1,...,8}
Position: (rank, file) = (row, column)
Algebraic: a1 = (1,1), h8 = (8,8)
```

### PAWN MOVEMENT MATRIX (White)
```
For pawn at (r,c):
Forward: (r+1, c) if r < 8 and empty
Double: (r+2, c) if r = 2 and path empty
Capture: (r+1, c±1) if opponent piece present
En passant: (r+1, c±1) under special conditions

Movement matrix M_pawn(r,c):
M_pawn(r,c)[i][j] = 
1 if (i,j) = (r+1,c) and B[r+1][c] = 0
1 if (i,j) = (r+2,c) and r=2 and B[r+1][c]=B[r+2][c]=0
1 if (i,j) = (r+1,c±1) and B[r+1][c±1] ∈ Opponent
0 otherwise
```

### KNIGHT MOVEMENT MATRIX
```
Knight moves in L-shape: ±(2,1) or ±(1,2)
M_knight(r,c)[i][j] = 1 if |i-r|+|j-c|=3 and |i-r|×|j-c|=2
and B[i][j] ∉ Friendly
```

### BISHOP MOVEMENT MATRIX
```
Bishop moves diagonally: along lines where |i-r| = |j-c|
M_bishop(r,c)[i][j] = 1 if |i-r| = |j-c| > 0
and all squares between (r,c) and (i,j) are empty
and B[i][j] ∉ Friendly
```

### ROOK MOVEMENT MATRIX
```
Rook moves orthogonally: i=r or j=c
M_rook(r,c)[i][j] = 1 if (i=r XOR j=c) and not both
and all squares between (r,c) and (i,j) are empty
and B[i][j] ∉ Friendly
```

### QUEEN MOVEMENT MATRIX
```
Queen = Bishop ∪ Rook
M_queen = M_bishop ∨ M_rook
```

### KING MOVEMENT MATRIX
```
King moves one square in any direction: |i-r| ≤ 1, |j-c| ≤ 1
Castling: Special case
M_king(r,c)[i][j] = 1 if max(|i-r|,|j-c|) = 1
and B[i][j] ∉ Friendly
and square not under attack
```

