### BALL-TO-BALL COLLISIONS

#### Position of Contact Point
```
Given balls A and B at positions (x₁, y₁) and (x₂, y₂):
Contact point C = (x₁, y₁) + r × (x₂ - x₁, y₂ - y₁) / d
where d = √((x₂ - x₁)² + (y₂ - y₁)²)
```

#### Angle of Impact
```
Angle from A to B: φ = arctan2(y₂ - y₁, x₂ - x₁)
Angle of incidence = φ
Angle of reflection depends on cut angle
