### BALL-BALL COLLISION PHYSICS

#### Conservation of Momentum
```
m₁v₁ + m₂v₂ = m₁v₁' + m₂v₂'
Since m₁ = m₂ = m (same mass):
v₁ + v₂ = v₁' + v₂'
```

#### Conservation of Energy (Elastic Collision)
```
½m₁v₁² + ½m₂v₂² = ½m₁v₁'² + ½m₂v₂'²
```

#### Final Velocities
```
For head-on collision (balls aligned):
v₁' = [(m₁ - m₂)v₁ + 2m₂v₂]/(m₁ + m₂)
v₂' = [(m₂ - m₁)v₂ + 2m₁v₁]/(m₁ + m₂)

For cut shot with angle θ:
v₁' = v₁ cos²θ + v₂ sin²θ
v₂' = v₁ sin²θ + v₂ cos²θ
```

#### Cut Angle Formula
```
θ = arcsin(b/d) where:
b = aiming offset (distance from center-to-center line)
d = distance between ball centers
```

### FRICTION EFFECTS

#### Sliding Friction
```
F_friction = μ_s × N
a_friction = -μ_s × g
v(t) = v₀ - μ_s × g × t
```

